---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About FuryStack">
  <div class="page-template">
    <div class="site-nav-main">
      <div class="inner" style="padding: 0 5vw;">
        <SiteNav />
      </div>
    </div>

    <main class="page-main">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <h1>About FuryStack</h1>
        <div class="page-content">
          <p class="lead">
            FuryStack is an open-source full-stack framework designed to build complex web solutions fast and easily.
          </p>
          <p>
            The main goal of FuryStack is to bring enterprise-grade architecture to the NodeJS Ecosystem with a pack of separated but perfectly matched parts.
            You can build a modern scalable backend service in no-time and a responsive SPA frontend without bloating your app with 3rd party
            and low quality, often abandoned dependencies. Developer experience is the main focus while the framework also tries to encourage keeping the code
            clean and decoupled.
          </p>
          <p>
            FuryStack contains all the basic parts that you need to start with &mdash; like DI/IOC, authentication, data stores, entity authorization, logging, etc.
            If you want to use only a subset of the layers (e.g. only the Dependency Injection) you can also pick the one you like.
          </p>
          <p>
            In FuryStack, there are some concepts that are not very common nowadays &mdash; like sharing REST API definitions
            with type checking between the service and the frontend in a monorepo.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-template { display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 100vh; }

  .page-main {
    flex-grow: 1;
    padding: calc(64px + 48px) 5vw 80px;
    background: #fff;
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) { .page-main { background: var(--color-darkmode); } }

  .page-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-inner h1 {
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    font-size: 3.6rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .page-inner h1 { font-size: 2.6rem; } }

  .page-content {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-body);
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) { .page-content { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72); } }

  .lead {
    font-size: 2.1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-darkgrey);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) { .lead { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85); } }
</style>
